
libxml2 is an interface unit that will allow Pascal developers to work with XML using the GNOME library libxml2.

The intention is to keep it in sync with any changes in original C headers.

You can find here:

libxml2:              the header translation for libxml2.dll / libxml2.so
libxslt:              dito for libxslt.dll /libxslt.so
dom2:                 a dom2 compliant interface and implementations based on libxml2 and msdom
demos/data            xml-files (and more data files), used by the demo programs
demos/libxml2/demo1   a simple xpath demo for the using libxml2
demos/dom2/test       a graphical testsuite, testing 98 of 100 dom2 functions and more
msxml                 a msxml compliant interface and an implementation based on libxml2
msxmldom              depreciated
wrappers              depreciated


